<subSubSection id="C480720B13498E219615D0E11BFFE710" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="045EB7B48154ED87A1EB9CFE7C1DDC5F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2011F6A072E9437F04230F5838AF4D27" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
2.4 mm long (n = 1); 3.0
<normalizedToken id="6A9C691C0BB779D539A7ABA464886462" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by its slender form; pronotum from dorsal view elongate, anterior margin rounded (type 7); outer margin of protibiae distinctly triangular, bearing five denticles, denticles not contiguous; and declivital strial punctures very large, coarse.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
